%% RFID Event Processing Pipeline
%% Shows the journey of a single tag detection from reader to dashboard

sequenceDiagram
    participant Tag as 📋 RFID Tag<br/>(on case file)
    participant Reader as 📡 Fixed Reader<br/>(under desk)
    participant GW as 🖥️ Edge Gateway<br/>(Raspberry Pi)
    participant MQTT as ☁️ IoT Core<br/>(MQTT Broker)
    participant Lambda as ⚡ Event Processor<br/>(Lambda)
    participant DB as 🗄️ DynamoDB
    participant API as 🌐 REST API
    participant Dash as 🖥️ Dashboard

    Note over Tag,Reader: File placed on Clerk Room 3, Table 1

    Reader->>Reader: RF field energizes tag antenna
    Tag-->>Reader: Backscatter: Tag ID + RSSI
    Note right of Reader: Tag: 4A:7B:2C:9F<br/>RSSI: -35 dBm

    Reader->>GW: LLRP TagReportData
    
    GW->>GW: Deduplication check
    Note right of GW: First detection of this<br/>tag at this reader?<br/>YES → publish

    GW->>MQTT: MQTT Publish (QoS 1)<br/>Topic: courthouse/rfid/events
    Note right of GW: Payload: {tag_id, reader_id,<br/>rssi_dbm, timestamp}

    MQTT->>Lambda: IoT Rule triggers Lambda

    Lambda->>Lambda: 1. Validate event
    Lambda->>Lambda: 2. Add to RSSI sliding window
    Lambda->>Lambda: 3. Compute median RSSI per reader
    Lambda->>Lambda: 4. Compare readers, apply 6dBm threshold
    Note right of Lambda: Reader CLK-RM3-T1: median -35 dBm<br/>Reader CLK-RM3-T2: median -55 dBm<br/>Margin: 20 dBm > 6 dBm<br/>→ HIGH confidence

    Lambda->>DB: 5. Get previous location
    DB-->>Lambda: Previous: Judge Bench
    Note right of Lambda: Location changed!<br/>→ Write DEPARTURE + ARRIVAL

    Lambda->>DB: 6. Update file_locations (current)
    Lambda->>DB: 7. Write file_movements (DEPARTURE from bench)
    Lambda->>DB: 8. Write file_movements (ARRIVAL at clerk desk)

    Dash->>API: GET /files/4A:7B:2C:9F/location
    API->>DB: Query file_locations
    DB-->>API: {location: "Clerk Room 3 - Table 1", confidence: "HIGH"}
    API-->>Dash: 200 OK + location data
    
    Note over Dash: Dashboard shows file<br/>at Clerk Room 3, Table 1<br/>with movement history
